<h2>How to compare states without misleading assumptions</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Hold inputs constant:</strong> Use the same home price, down payment, and interest rate to compare states consistently.</li>
<li><strong>Check local costs:</strong> Property taxes, insurance, and HOA fees vary by county and lender.</li>
<li><strong>Validate with local sources:</strong> Confirm tax and insurance estimates before making decisions.</li>
<li><strong>Model multiple scenarios:</strong> Run conservative and optimistic cases to understand the range.</li>
</ul>
